Taiwan to Scrap Rule on Face Value of Stocks, Times Reports

-- B y   A n d r e a   W o n g
-- 
2011-03-15T00:44:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/taiwan-to-scrap-rule-on-face-value-of-stocks-times-reports.html
The  Taiwan Stock Exchange  will
scrap the rule on the face value of stocks, the Commercial Times
reported, citing Chairman Schive Chi. Taiwan stocks have a face
value of NT$10, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Wong at 
